               <head>Miscellany</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85102543 lccn.loc.gov/sh85077734">
                  <summary>Judeo-Persian biblical and liturgical poems followed by a list of Malay numbers.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="he" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="9r" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                     <title xml:lang="jpr">מונאגת נאמה גומגומה </title>
                     <title>Munājāt-nāmah Jumjumah</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>'Book of Devotions' on Jumjumah. The story of Jumjumah in Judeo-Persian verse. The tale is frequently found in Judeo-Persian manuscripts and attributed (by Jes P. Asmussen) to <persName key="viaf_120724759 http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759">Farīd al-Dīn ʿAṭṭār</persName>.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Asmussen, Jes Peter, <title>Studies in Judeo-Persian literature</title> (Leiden: Brill, 1973), pp. 76-87.
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="9v" to="15r" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                     <title xml:lang="jpr">מונאגת נאמה מוסה ע"ה </title>
                     <title>Munājāt-nāmah Musah</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>'Book of Devotions' on Moses. A poem about Moses (Biblical leader), here misattributed to <persName key="viaf_120724759 http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759">Farīd al-Dīn ʿAṭṭār</persName>.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="15v" to="24r" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                     <title xml:lang="he">תפסיר דודי יארד</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tafsīr dodi yarad</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>A paraphrase of a religious poem.</p>
                        <p>Continuation: ff. 25r-28r.</p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon>בהאגת דר תעגיל באז כר אימה ... דר מודש ניסן בפדיס ... עשק כה אדר תרס"א - רחמים יעקב ... <locus n="24r" />
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus n="24v" />
                     <textLang mainLang="zsm-Hebr" otherLangs="he" />
                     <title>Text in Malay(?) in Hebrew characters.</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="he">בהזרת השם יתברך</incipit>
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p />
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="25r" to="28r" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                     <title>Continuation of the Tafsīr.</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p />
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="28v" to="32v" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                     <title>Wedding poems in Judeo-Persian</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="he">שירות חתאני </incipit>
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p />
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="33r" to="48r" />
                     <textLang mainLang="jpr" otherLangs="zsm-Hebr" />
                     <title>Persian-Malay vocabulary in Hebrew characters</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>This is the only known text in Malay in Hebrew characters.</p>
                        <p>List of numbers: satu, duʾah, tigah, hampah, nimah, etc.</p>
                        <p>It has been filmed in the series of <title>Microfilms of Malay Manuscripts from the British Library, Oriental and India Office Collections</title>, presented by the British Council, Brunei Darussalam, 1992, film no. O/C Pos. 310/A.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
